1) Mobile device and your computer with TS must be in the same Network Area. You have to use WiFi to connect to the same router.\n

Remember to keep connection in good condition! 
All kinds of Torrents, firewall, antivirus can slow down app responsibility or even suspend it.

There are two possibilities to connect with external TS3 server:
1) as serveradmin - he has access to main Server and all VirtualServers running on it.
2) as serverquery delegate.

If you are login as serveradmin leave a 0 in Port(optional).
If you are login as queryDelegate put port number in Port(optional) under which VirtualServer is running, for example: 9987.

If you leave a 0 in Port(optional), you declare that you are serveradmin, and after connect, there will show a list with available VirtualServers to connect.
Changing Port(optional) mean that you are queryDelegate with admin privilages and you can connect ONLY to virtual server with specific port address.

Only ServerAdmin has possibility to stop and start virtual server.

Examples...

1)ServerAdmin

Server Address: 12.123.43.222
Query port: 10011
Port(optional): 0
Username: serveradmin
Password: xxxxxxxxxxx


2)QueryDelegate:

Server Address: 12.123.43.222
Query port: 10011
Port(optional): 9987
Username: mynickname
Password: xxxxxxxxxx


How to create a ServerQuery Login?
On menu bar of your TS3 select Tools and ServerQuery Login.
Put a custom login name and on the next step you will get password.
Give this information to your admin or moderator or even client, if he has a need to control TS3 server by TSmobile app.

If you have any problems or you found errors just contact with me.
You can write review my app on GooglePlay or give me info what would you like to have in next updates.

Have fun!

2) First of all run TS on your PC, connect to the selected server and go to the channel on which the conversation will be carried out. 

In TS's configuration has to be enabled ClientQuery and TS control plugin. The above-mentioned options are enabled by default after installation the TS program. 
Go to Settings -> Plugins:
In Settings of ClientQuery is very important to check as enabled Open telnet Port for everyone. \n\nConfirm all changes and click on Reload All button.
\n\nAfter that you are ready to push the Find button on mobile device and choose IP of your PC or Laptop where TS is running.

Configure TeamSpeak3 Client on your PC as shown below in instruction.
Your PC must be connected to router by cable (Ethernet) or Wifi. Your mobile device must be connected to the same router as your PC (in this case only by WiFi). 
Run searching "Find"-button, to find TeamSpeak3 software running on any PC in your local area network. 
If there is any results, try again with search few times, max 5 attempts, after that your configuration is wrong. Check it with instruction or with movie on Youtube.

Remember! You cannot do this if you have no rights to configure your home router.

First, check what is the IP address of your computer, for Windows OS run "cmd" then enter "ipconfig", and save somewhere "address IPv4", it will be something like: 192.168.1.110. 
Second, check what is your public IP, for example use www.whatismyipaddress.com. It will be something like: 99.152.312.8. 
Connect by your PC to home router and setup the Port Range Forwarding. Protocol - [TCP], Port Range from - [25639] to - [25639], IP address - [Your local IP], enable this rule and save it. 

After all steps, use mobile app TSmobile and on the "Client" view, touch "Use 3G"-button (Top-Right corner). There will appear "Add Your IP"-button where you have to enter your public address IP. 
Your firewall software on PC need to gives you access to use port 25639 and has it unlocked. 

Soon there will be video on youtube with step by step configuration.
